Granting the sudo permission to Non-sudo users
----------------------------------------------

Step 1: In the terminal open type:
         $ sudo visudo

Step 2: At the end of file:
         username ALL=(ALL) ALL 
         
Step 3: Ctrl+o to save the file 

Step 4: Done !! 

Note:  Whenever you want to remove the user from sudo follow step 1 and remove the added line (shown in step 2) associated to that non-sudo user
